## Core Features

### Feature 1: Plain Text, Resets, and Concealment

**As a developer**, I want to render ordinary log text and non-printing ANSI sequences into safe visible output, so I can display exactly what users should see in a browser log without exposing hidden control text.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is an object with `operation` set to `render_html`, a `palette`, and a `text` string. The output is the rendered HTML/text stream exactly as it should appear. Empty text produces empty output; ordinary text is unchanged; reset-only and cursor-clearing sequences produce no visible output; conceal mode hides normal concealed text; embedded console-note marker payloads are preserved when the original behavior treats them as protected log metadata; character-set reset sequences are filtered while their surrounding visible characters remain.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature1_plain_reset_and_conceal.json`

```json
{
  "description": "Render ordinary text, reset-only input, and concealed segments so that visible text is preserved while hidden ANSI text is omitted unless it is an embedded console note marker.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":""},
      "expected_output": ""
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"line"},
      "expected_output": "line"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"[a specific Unicode escape sequence representing the ANSI reset command — ask the implementation team for the exact character sequence]\u001b[K"},
      "expected_output": ""
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"there is concealed text here, \u001b[8mCONCEAL[a specific Unicode escape sequence representing the ANSI reset command — ask the implementation team for the exact character sequence], and it should vanish."},
      "expected_output": "there is concealed text here, , and it should vanish."
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"there is a ConsoleNote here, \u001b[8mha:CONSOLENOTE[a specific Unicode escape sequence representing the ANSI reset command — ask the implementation team for the exact character sequence], and it should be left untouched."},
      "expected_output": "there is a ConsoleNote here, \u001b[8mha:CONSOLENOTE[a specific Unicode escape sequence representing the ANSI reset command — ask the implementation team for the exact character sequence], and it should be left untouched."
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"(\u001b(0)"},
      "expected_output": "()"
    }
  ]
}
```

