### Feature 2: Text Attribute Rendering

**As a developer**, I want to convert ANSI text attributes into HTML style markup, so I can preserve emphasis, underlines, borders, strikeout, overline, and faint intensity in rendered logs.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a `render_html` object containing ANSI SGR text-attribute sequences. The output is the exact HTML fragment emitted for the visible text. Bold, underline, double underline, italic, strikeout, framed, overlined, and faint attributes open the corresponding HTML tags or styled spans and close when their matching reset code appears or when the stream ends.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature2_text_attributes.json`

```json
