### Feature 3: Palette-Based Color Rendering

**As a developer**, I want to render ANSI foreground and background colors with selectable palettes, so I can match terminal colors in HTML output across basic, bright, indexed, and RGB color forms.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a `render_html` object with a named palette and ANSI color sequences in `text`. The output is the exact HTML fragment with `color` and `background-color` styles. Basic foreground/background colors use the selected palette; CSS-style palettes emit CSS color names; bright colors use bright palette entries; 256-color indexed values and 24-bit RGB values render deterministic hex colors independent of palette names.

