### Feature 4: Independent Resets, Nested Styles, and Inverse Video

**As a developer**, I want to combine overlapping ANSI attributes without losing active styles, so I can display complex terminal styling correctly even when colors and text attributes overlap.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a `render_html` object containing overlapping color, bold, underline, reset, and inverse-video sequences. The output is the exact HTML fragment after preserving active styles across independent foreground/background resets. Foreground reset removes only foreground color, background reset removes only background color, nesting is repaired so HTML remains properly ordered, and inverse video swaps effective foreground/background colors until inverse mode is disabled or fully reset.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature4_resets_nesting_and_inverse.json`

```json
{
  "description": "Preserve style nesting across overlapping ANSI attributes, reset foreground and background independently, and invert foreground/background colors when inverse video is active.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[32mtic\u001b[1mtac\u001b[39mtoe"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"color: #00CD00;\">tic<b>tac</b></span><b>toe</b>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[42mtic\u001b[1mtac\u001b[49mtoe"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"background-color: #00CD00;\">tic<b>tac</b></span><b>toe</b>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"plain\u001b[32mgreen\u001b[1mboldgreen\u001b[4mulboldgreen\u001b[31mulboldred\u001b[22mulred\u001b[24mred"},
      "expected_output": "plain<span style=\"color: #00CD00;\">green<b>boldgreen<u>ulboldgreen</u></b></span><b><u><span style=\"color: #CD0000;\">ulboldred</span></u></b><u><span style=\"color: #CD0000;\">ulred</span></u><span style=\"color: #CD0000;\">red</span>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[7mon\u001b[moff"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"background-color: currentColor;\"><span style=\"color: #FFFFFF;\">on</span></span>off"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[33;41;7mon\u001b[27moff"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"color: #CDCD00;\"><span style=\"background-color: #CD0000;\"></span></span><span style=\"background-color: #CDCD00; color: #CD0000;\">on</span><span style=\"background-color: #CD0000; color: #CDCD00;\">off</span>"
    }
  ]
}
```

