### Feature 5: Default Palette Wrapping and Unicode Preservation

**As a developer**, I want to apply palette defaults and preserve international text, so I can render logs with default terminal background/foreground while keeping Unicode content intact.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a `render_html` object using a palette that may define default foreground and background colors. If defaults exist, each rendered stream is wrapped in a container carrying those default colors; otherwise no default wrapper is added. Non-ASCII text, including accented Latin text, Japanese text, and emoji, remains unchanged while surrounding ANSI styling is applied.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature5_default_wrapping_and_unicode.json`

```json
{
  "description": "When a palette defines default foreground and background colors, wrap rendered output in a container using those defaults and preserve non-ASCII text while applying ANSI styling.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"vga","text":"\u001b[32mtic\u001b[1mtac\u001b[39mtoe"},
      "expected_output": "<div style=\"background-color: #000000;color: #AAAAAA;\"><span style=\"color: #00AA00;\">tic<b>tac</b></span><b>toe</b></div>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"vga","text":"\u001b[7mon\u001b[moff"},
      "expected_output": "<div style=\"background-color: #000000;color: #AAAAAA;\"><span style=\"background-color: #AAAAAA; color: #000000;\">on</span>off</div>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[32mmünchen"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"color: #00CD00;\">münchen</span>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[32mこんにちは"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"color: #00CD00;\">こんにちは</span>"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"render_html","palette":"xterm","text":"\u001b[94;1m[ INFO ] 😀😀[a specific Unicode escape sequence representing the ANSI reset command — ask the implementation team for the exact character sequence]😀"},
      "expected_output": "<span style=\"color: #4682B4;\"><b>[ INFO ] 😀😀</b></span>😀"
    }
  ]
}
```

