### Feature 8: Hidden Log Action Markers

**As a developer**, I want to insert hidden action markers into log text, so I can allow a log renderer to carry colorizing state changes at exact character positions.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is an `insert_action_marker` object containing `text`, `position`, `palette`, and `action`. The output is a single `annotated_text=` line containing the original text with a hidden action marker inserted at the requested character position. The marker identifier is normalized to `<id>` so the contract validates marker placement and shape rather than a random identifier value.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature8_action_marker_rendering.json`

```json
{
  "description": "Insert a hidden colorizing action marker into annotated log text at the requested character position, producing stable markup around a normalized action identifier.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {"operation":"insert_action_marker","text":"abc123","position":4,"palette":"vga","action":"start"},
      "expected_output": "annotated_text=abc1<div data-ansicolor-action=\"<id>\"></div>23\n"
    },
    {
      "input": {"operation":"insert_action_marker","text":"Log line","position":0,"palette":"xterm","action":"stop"},
      "expected_output": "annotated_text=<div data-ansicolor-action=\"<id>\"></div>Log line\n"
    }
  ]
}
```

